&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are: &lt;/strong&gt;Axis Automation leverages the teamwork of our leading engineers and machine builders to conceptualize, design, integrate, deploy and service factory automation systems for forward-thinking manufacturing customers. Our team has decades of automation experience, spanning hundreds of projects and thousands of automation configurations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Mission: &lt;/strong&gt;Supporting the adoption of automation solutions that empower people and enhance productivity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Vision: &lt;/strong&gt;To be the leading automation solutions provider for the manufacturing community&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we are looking for: &lt;/strong&gt;A career-oriented and motivated &lt;strong&gt;Account Manager &lt;/strong&gt;to join a dynamic, tight- knit team engineering and integrating custom factory automation equipment supporting customers in general industries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Account Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development and acquisition of new customers in general non-automotive industries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain good standing and growing relationships with existing/acquired customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate new project orders to meet or exceed annual goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cooperatively and collaboratively with all team members, customer and supplier partners throughout project acquisition and delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide metrics, reports and success criteria for sales and related activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic planning and goal-setting surrounding market and customer sector-specific targeting and communication initiatives to close or grow customer accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain &amp;amp; submit appropriate records for forecasting, quote status &amp;amp; expenses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist Applications Engineering team as needed in developing solutions to customers’ needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support marketing efforts and general proactive market outreach activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Existing relationships with key customers and decision-makers in engineering and procurement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A general understanding of manufacturing, particularly as it pertains to automation equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to continually contact prospective customers and develop relevant leads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional skills in organizing and leading conversations and building trust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven, and superior interpersonal, written and verbal communication abilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sense of diplomacy, including negotiation skills, conflict resolution and people management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess a creative and solutions-oriented approach to project opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel to support customers in order to meet project sales goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to skillfully utilize CRM software and Microsoft applications notably Excel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Champion Our Operating Principles: You will be expected to actively embody and uphold our ten Operating Principles, which guide our every action and decision at Axis Automation. These principles are key to our culture and success.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation: &lt;/strong&gt;Base salary, sales commission, year-end discretionary bonus&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits: &lt;/strong&gt;Paid-time off, 401(k) employer match, Health Insurance, Dental Insurance, Vision Insurance, Short-term and long-term disability, Parental l

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications Engineer Level 2&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Axis leverages the teamwork of our leading engineers and machine builders to conceptualize, design, integrate, deploy and service factory automation systems for forward-thinking manufacturing customers. Our team has decades of automation experience, spanning hundreds of projects and thousands of automation configurations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Applications Engineer Level 2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description: &lt;/strong&gt;The Applications Engineer Level 2 will work within the Applications Engineering department to configure manufacturing system proposals and support the Axis team through the deployment of awarded solutions. This engineer must have some experience in industrial automation/manufacturing or related field. Requires knowledge of project budgeting, custom automated equipment, along with manufacturing processes and equipment. Relevant engineering disciplines include controls, mechanical, industrial and welding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities Include&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare detailed automated assembly equipment proposals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interact with suppliers and cross functional team members to solicit input establishing project proposals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare process steps, concept generation, budget, and cycle time analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify labor hour requirements, material requirements, risk, cost and timing for each project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Obtain external quotes from vendor base, find new support sources and advance process technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand customer expectations and convey to fellow team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead quote and project related meetings as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support project kickoff, build and engineering teams with concept and customer specifics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in expanding workable libraries for actual cost feedback loop to improve estimating&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently support customer visits and meetings (occasionally off-site at customers facility)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional management of customer relationships and requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active in building customer relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Real-time communication with company management on developments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion our Operating Principles: You will be expected to actively embody and uphold our ten Operating Principles, which guide our every action and decision at Axis Automation. These principles are key to our culture and success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Experience Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is subject to the International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) which requires U.S. person status. ITAR defines U.S. person as a U.S. Citizen, U.S. Permanent Resident (i.e. &#39;Green Card Holder&#39;), Political Asylee, or Refugee.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelors’ Degree in Engineering-related field – Or comparable field experience in similar role with exposure to industrial automation systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-3 years of experience with project management, budgeting and quoting custom automated equipment or similar responsibilities within relevant industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable of working independently in a self-directed manner while contributing as part of a team to achieve common goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with speaking technically in front of groups (co-workers &amp;amp; customers)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competent with Microsoft Office Applications (Excel/Word)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with automated processes and equipment

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Controls Electrician&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;-Open Position -&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Axis Automation leverages the teamwork of our leading engineers and machine builders to conceptualize, design, integrate, deploy and service factory automation systems for forward-thinking manufacturing customers. Our team has decades of automation experience, spanning hundreds of projects and thousands of automation configurations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Controls Electrician&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description:&lt;/strong&gt; The Controls Electrician serves as a team member in the electrical assembly process for automation equipment and this electrician is responsible for panel building and wiring of electrical components used on automation equipment projects. Willing to train entry level candidate with electrical knowledge.&lt;br&gt;•Serves as a Controls Electrician team member in the electrical assembly process for automation equipment&lt;br&gt;•Assemble &amp;amp; wire electrical panels and machine wiring according to approved design and customer specifications.&lt;br&gt;•Ensure that changes and problems get documented and communicated.&lt;br&gt;•Communicate with the project team on open issues and progress during the build process.&lt;br&gt;•Assist with the successful execution of equipment builds including cost, quality, timing, and customer satisfaction.&lt;br&gt;•Effectively and safely troubleshoot wiring and circuits&lt;br&gt;•Read and understand schematics&lt;br&gt;•Problem solve issues / poke yokes / cycle time&lt;br&gt;•Travel for install and runoffs with customer&lt;br&gt;•Identify electrical problems, and recommend adjustments/repair work as necessary&lt;br&gt;•Work cross-functionally with all departments during all phases of the project including de-bug and runoff&lt;br&gt;•Champion Our Operating Principles: You will be expected to actively embody and uphold our ten Operating Principles, which guide our every action and decision at Axis Automation. These principles are key to our culture and success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Experience Requested:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;•High school diploma or equivalent certificate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Preferred two (2) years electrical experience with equipment building&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Team player, able to take direction and be self-directed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•High regard for safety standards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Willingness to travel up to 20% (local, national, international)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt; $20.00 - $32.00/hour (Wage dependent on experience)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt; Overtime pay, travel pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt; Axis offers a comprehensive benefits package with no waiting period.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Job Description&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Controls Engineer, Level 2/3&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Axis Automation is looking for career-oriented Controls Engineers to join a dynamic, tight-knit team creating custom factory automation equipment. We&#39;re a company with big ambitions - plenty of opportunities for growth and advancement!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Axis leverages the teamwork of our leading engineers and machine builders to conceptualize, design, integrate, deploy and service factory automation systems for forward-thinking manufacturing customers. Our team has decades of automation experience, spanning hundreds of projects and thousands of automation configurations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description: &lt;/strong&gt;Controls Engineers work with peer groups, Project Managers, Mechanical Engineers, Builders, Technicians and other personnel to design, implement and document control systems for various types of automation and robotic equipment. You will be personally involved with electrical, pneumatic and hydraulic system design, simulation, PLC, HMI, robotic and peripheral device programming, machine debug and validation / buyoff. Travel to customer sites for installation, startup, and support of equipment represents 10-20% of time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Controls Engineer, Level 2/3&lt;/u&gt;: Minimum 2 years of experience in Controls Engineering and Controls Design, with recognized technical expertise, ability to lead larger projects, interface with customers, support other team members, and be a self-starter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aid in the development of electrical, pneumatic, and hydraulic system designs of automated work cells.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implements tasks in PLC (ladder / basic structured text), HMI, and robot programs within established architecture and standards; performs I/O mapping, device setup, alarms/diagnostics, basic data handling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret customer specifications and communicate effectively to produce machinery that meets both customer and Axis Automation specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs first-pass troubleshooting using schematics and code; documents findings and escalates with clear context.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adheres to code / electrical standards; keeps backups/change logs, I/O and tag maps, and manuals current for assigned scope.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists with offline/online debug, device bring-up, FAT/SAT support, and on-site startup under supervision; follows test&amp;nbsp;procedures and records results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional management of customer relationships and requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with vendors to specify and source major purchased components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works constructively with Mechanical, Electrical, Build and Project Management to resolve issues and protect milestones.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Champion Our Operating Principles: You will be expected to actively embody and uphold our ten Operating Principles, which guide our every action and decision at Axis Automation. These principles are key to our culture and success.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in related engineering field strongly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years’ experience in a Controls / automation focused role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing to travel approximately 10%-20%&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Skills

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Controls Electrician&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Axis Automation leverages the teamwork of our leading engineers and machine builders to conceptualize, design, integrate, deploy and service factory automation systems for forward-thinking manufacturing customers. Our team has decades of automation experience, spanning hundreds of projects and thousands of automation configurations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead Controls Electrician&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Description:&lt;/strong&gt; The Lead Controls Electrician serves as a team member in the electrical assembly process for automation equipment. This electrician is responsible for panel building and wiring of electrical components used on automation equipment projects.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;•Lead and guide electrical team members across multiple projects&lt;br&gt;•Monitor build progress to ensure timelines are met&lt;br&gt;•Act as the primary communicator for electrical status and open issues during the build process&lt;br&gt;•Support onboarding and mentoring of new team members&lt;br&gt;•Build and wire custom panels and systems per design and spec&lt;br&gt;•Interpret and follow electrical schematics and customer documentation&lt;br&gt;•Troubleshoot and resolve electrical issues efficiently and effectively.&lt;br&gt;•Document changes and communicate updates throughout the build process&lt;br&gt;•Support project success by focusing on quality, cost, and customer satisfaction&lt;br&gt;•Collaborate with cross-functional teams through all stages of the project&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Participate in on-site installations &amp;amp; Support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Champion Our Operating Principles: You will be expected to actively embody and uphold our ten Operating Principles, which guide our every action and decision at Axis Automation. These principles are key to our culture and success.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;•&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; 4 years of hands-on experience wiring custom automated machinery&lt;br&gt;•Proven ability to lead and coordinate a team&lt;br&gt;•Strong troubleshooting and problem-solving skills&lt;br&gt;•High attention to safety and detail&lt;br&gt;•Comfortable reading schematics and working with complex mechanical systems&lt;br&gt;•Basic computer proficiency (Excel, Word, OneNote)&lt;br&gt;•Team player with strong communication and self-direction&lt;br&gt;•Willingness to travel up to 20% (local, national, international)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt; $32.00 - $40.00/hour (Wage based on Experience)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt; Overtime pay, travel pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt; Axis offers a comprehensive benefits package with no waiting period.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Machine Builder Level 3&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;- Position Description -&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview: &lt;/strong&gt;The Machine Builder Level 3 is a mid-level individual contributor who owns larger sub-systems and complete machines with modest oversight. This builder actively contributes to mechanical debug, supports FAT/SAT activities, mentors newer builders informally, and engages directly with engineering and project management to resolve build issues and protect schedules. This builder is trusted on customer sites for installation support. This position reports directly to the Build Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Builds larger sub-systems and complete machines from prints and BOMs with modest oversight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads mechanical debug on assigned scope; performs root cause analysis on assembly and mechanical issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports FAT/SAT activities: participates in test procedures, documents results, and helps resolve punch-list items&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engages directly with mechanical design engineers, controls engineers, Controls Technicians, and project management to resolve build issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travels to customer sites for installation support, including domestic and international destinations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentors Machine Builder I and II informally; demonstrates techniques and shares tribal knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifies and escalates design issues that complicate builds; redlines prints accurately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains build documentation: change notes, discrepancy reports, and as-built records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operates all standard shop equipment safely and effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follows LOTO and shop safety procedures; reinforces safety culture across the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular lifting of objects 50 lbs or more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion our Operating Principles: You will be expected to actively embody and uphold our ten Operating Principles, which guide our every action and decision at Axis Automation. These principles are key to our culture and success.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; High school diploma or equivalent required. Vocational or technical training valued.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 3–5 years building custom industrial equipment or machines, with exposure to multiple project life cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mechanical Assembly:&lt;/strong&gt; Builds complete machines from prints with minimal oversight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pneumatics:&lt;/strong&gt; Installs, routes, and troubleshoots pneumatic systems independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Print Reading &amp;amp; GD&amp;amp;T:&lt;/strong&gt; Fluent in mechanical and pneumatic prints; uses GD&amp;amp;T effectively; redlines accurately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shop Tools:&lt;/strong&gt; Proficient with all standard shop equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mechanical Debug:&lt;/strong&gt; Leads debug on assigned scope; performs root cause analysis on mechanical issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FAT/SAT:&lt;/strong&gt; Active participant in factory and site acceptance testing; resolves punch-list items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Robotics Integration:&lt;/strong&gt; Familiar with installation and integration of robotics build integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Safety:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong LOTO practice; thorough understanding of robotic cell safety standards.&lt;/li

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mechanical Engineer, Levels 2-3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Title(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Mechanical Engineer Levels 2-3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Position Description: &lt;/strong&gt;Mechanical Engineers of all levels work with other Mechanical Engineers, Project Managers, Controls Engineers, Builders, Technicians and other personnel to conceptualize, design, test and validate automation systems for various types of automation and robotic equipment. You will be involved with developing and fully designing equipment, layouts and subassemblies of automated robotic work cells.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities: Levels 2 and 3&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;• Develop 3D models and 2D drawings for robotic EOAT, fixtures, and automation components using CAD software (e.g., SolidWorks), ensuring precision and optimal performance.&lt;br&gt;• Evaluate designs through stress simulations, motion studies, and safety assessments (e.g., FMEA) to ensure reliability in real-world applications.&lt;br&gt;• Work with cross-functional teams to integrate mechanical systems with electrical and controls frameworks, delivering seamless, high-performance solutions.&lt;br&gt;• Spearhead prototype testing and iterative refinements, transforming concepts into durable, deployable designs.&lt;br&gt;• Create clear technical documentation, including specifications, engineering changes ensuring traceability and project alignment.&lt;br&gt;• Assist on-site operations, troubleshoot issues, and provide hands-on technical support to internal teams.&lt;br&gt;• Complete tasks on schedule and within budget, proposing innovative enhancements to improve efficiency and functionality&lt;br&gt;•Champion Our Operating Principles: You will be expected to actively embody and uphold our ten Operating Principles, which guide our every action and decision at Axis Automation. These principles are key to our culture and success.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Responsibilities: Level 3&lt;br&gt;• &lt;/strong&gt;Lead the creation of equipment layouts, subassemblies, and automation systems using SolidWorks CAD, ensuring precision, innovation, and project alignment.&lt;br&gt;• Maintain compliance with Axis standards and customer requirements, applying advanced techniques to improve system performance and reliability.&lt;br&gt;• Manage small-scale projects from concept to completion, managing timelines and team coordination under the Engineering Manager’s guidance.&lt;br&gt;• Oversee build, assembly, and testing phases, resolving technical challenges with analytical rigor and hands on expertise.&lt;br&gt;• Guide junior engineers, offering technical mentorship to boost team skills and project success.&lt;br&gt;• Perform risk assessments and design reviews, proactively resolving issues to ensure safe, robust system performance.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Experience Requirements&lt;br&gt;• Level 2: &lt;/strong&gt;1 - 4 years in mechanical design or automation, with a track record of tackling real-world engineering challenges&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Level 3: &lt;/strong&gt;Minimum 4 years in mechanical design and automation engineering&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• &lt;/strong&gt;Proven experience developing comprehensive design packages&lt;br&gt;• Proficiency in CAD software (SolidWorks preferred)&lt;br&gt;• Working knowledge of GD&amp;amp;T&lt;br&gt;• Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering preferred&lt;br&gt;• Experience with robotics, pneumatics, and automation system design.&lt;br&gt;• Proficiency in Microsoft Word and Excel for technical documentation and analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;$60,000 - $90,000&lt;/p&gt;
