&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Controls Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt; The Senior Controls Engineer is a high-impact individual contributor who designs, programs, commissions, debugs,&amp;nbsp;and deploys complex automation systems while informally mentoring junior engineers. A senior CE is capable of executing a project&amp;nbsp;independently throughout the entire project life cycle. The role serves as a technical cornerstone on multi-million-dollar projects, owning&amp;nbsp;electrical design, PLC/HMI/robot code, motion solutions, and safety compliance. This position reports directly to the Director of&amp;nbsp;Engineering.&lt;/p&gt;
